- Fixed detection of whether an HTTP resource exists. - Fixed HTTP connection leak.

Upgraded to jsch 0.1.2.  Should fix gump errors.

- FileContent changes:   - Added getAttributes() and getAttributeNames().   - Don't allow get/set last-modified time if the file is being written to.   - Don't allow get/set properties on files that don't exist.   - Allow get/set properties on files that are being read.   - Don't allow get certificates if the file is being written to. - Replaced AbstractFileObject.doGetAttribute() with doGetAttributes(). - Fixed Javadocs.

- FileObject.getType() no longer throws an exception if the file does not exist.   Instead, it returns FileType.IMAGINARY. - Added a bunch of capabilities discovery methods to FileType. - Tidied up some error methods.

Fixed some junction bugs: - Make sure FileObject.exists() returns true on junction point and ancestors after the   junction is added. - Don't fire create and delete events twice. - Fire create events on the junction point and ancestors when the junction is added.
- Fixed typo in file:// example. - Added a couple more examples.

Minor FileName tidy-ups: - Added FileName.SEPARATOR and SEPARATOR_CHAR constants - FileName.getRootUri() always returns a URI with trailing / - Made GenericFileName.getPort() return an int, rather than String - Fixed checking for empty share name for URI like smb://hostname/
Fixed doGetType() to check if the file exists.
- Fixed the jar and nested jar provider tests.  Reorganised layout of test files to do this. - Added a couple more concurrency tests.

- Added (slightly tweeked) maven-generated gump descriptor. - Fixed maven-generated build.xml.
